text.section:
Each licensee shall make and preserve the following books, accounts, and records for a period of at least 3 years:
A record of each payment instrument sold or issued;
A general ledger containing all assets, liability, capital, income, and expense accounts, which general ledger shall be posted at least monthly;
Settlement sheets received from each authorized delegate;
Bank statements and bank reconciliation records;
Records of outstanding payment instruments;
Records of each payment instrument paid within the 3-year period; and
A list of the names and addresses of all the licensee's authorized delegates, past and present.
